text.paragraph:
		     
	Patients Aged 12 weeks (3 months) and Older: See dosing regimens provided in Table 1. The every 12 hours regimen is recommended as it is associated with significantly less diarrhea [see 

                              Clinical Studies (14.2)
                           ]. However, the every 12 hours suspension (200 mg/5 mL and 400 mg/5 mL) and chewable tablets (200 mg and 400 mg) contain aspartame and should not be used by phenylketonurics. [see 

                              Warnings and Precautions (5.6)
                           ]

